news.title: PNB Housing's net profit rises 25.30% in Q4 FY25
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at ₹2,036.78 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 12.28 per cent from ₹1,813.97 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra government to acquire 8,000 acres land in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar: CM
news.para: Industries too are positive about coming here," the CM said. Speaking about infrastructure development in the city, he said a ring road will be constructed to connect industrial zones.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fall 0.5% in March
news.para: Private home prices fell 0.5% in March from the month before, following a revised 0.6% decline in February, data from the Rating and Valuation Department showed.

news.title: CCI Group invests ₹227 crore in logistics park in Sohna-Silani, Gurugram
news.para: Spanning approximately 9.5 lakh sq ft, the facility has features such as a clear height of 12 meters, FM2-grade flooring, cross dock multiple loading points, and wide internal RCC roads to support efficient vehicle circulation.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to transform 57 municipalities into smart cities with Rs 40,000 crore investment
news.para: The department has already developed 17 smart cities in line with this vision. The government allocated a budget of ₹40,000 crore for this project, with ₹145 crore already sanctioned as initial funding.

news.title: CorporatEdge launches 42,000 sq ft workspace in Delhi
news.para: With this, the company now operates eight centres across Delhi, Gurugram, and Bengaluru, collectively managing over 2,60,000 sq ft of workspace across the country.

news.title: Activists demand halt to illegal constructions in Bambolim, Goa
news.para: Placards in participants’ hands demanded freeing of pathways and scrapping of mega projects. A young protester holding his own placard said: stop cutting trees.

news.title: Hyderabad: GHMC faces surge in complaints on illegal structures and encroachments
news.para: Since Jan, citizens registered 955 complaints during Prajavani programme, with the town planning wing receiving 450 complaints among more than 15 different wings of the municipal corporation.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit up 9.57% in Q4 FY25
news.para: UltraTech Cement's net consolidated total income stood at ₹23,165.45 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 12.70 per cent from ₹20,554.55 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: VOX LINERIO SLAT PANELS- The Perfect Blend of Elegance and Functionality for Modern Interiors
news.para: At VOX, we offer inspiration, expert guidance, and complete interior design solutions, including coordinated sets of ceilings, walls, and flooring.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to build 2,500 new homes under Ramai Housing Scheme in FY26
news.para: The scheme, aimed at providing housing for Scheduled Castes and Neo-Buddhists, has already helped 5,795 families secure new homes.

news.title: Noida authority initiates the process of returning residential plots to 2,200 farmers
news.para: Officials said the case — marked by not just legal battles but bureaucratic hurdles too since the early 2000s — represented one of the longest-running land disputes in the region.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue department says ‘One State, One Registration’ scheme to be delayed
news.para: "It may take more than three to four months to ensure smooth rollout of the scheme," said a senior official of the revenue department, citing technical challenges delaying its statewide launch.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM urges all urban local bodies to offer uniform services to residents
news.para: Instructing officials to evolve a common fee structure, Yogi asked senior officers to begin working on the action plan. Currently, for instance, wide gaps can be seen in property transfer fees charged by different local bodies.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to geotag 24.46 lakh properties
news.para: Under the project, 18.30 lakh residential and 6.16 lakh non-residential properties will be geotagged, and an aerial 3D digital map of the city will also be created.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP carries out demolition drive around Sultanpur park
news.para: During the operation, two under-construction structures, 18 damp proof courses (DPCs), three farmhouse boundary walls, one industrial unit and five plot boundary walls were demolished.

news.title: Bengaluru property owners urge BBMP to extend 5% tax rebate
news.para: Residents argue that the BBMP property tax portal was inactive until April 5 due to technical glitches, leaving taxpayers with less time to make their payments.

news.title: Illegal layout properties to be confiscated, warns Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: Following a departmental review meeting, revenue minister Krishna Byregowda Friday said the decision follows strict directions from Supreme Court, which have been reiterated by chief minister Siddaramaiah.

news.title: Five more FIRs against Ansal Group in Lucknow for ₹5.78 crore fraud
news.para: So far about 70 cases has been lodged against the real estate firm in multi million land scam case. According to city-based businessman Sanjeev Agarwal , he paid Rs 5 crore in 2022 for a land deal.
